Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setGenerateViaMode(25.10)                            setGenerateViaMode(25.10)

Name
       setGenerateViaMode  - Auto-generates vias required by nanoroute for the
       default and non-default rules (NDRs)

Syntax
       setGenerateViaMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-auto {true|false}]

       [-ndr_only {true|false}]

       Auto-generates vias required by nanoroute for the default  and  non-de-
       fault  rules (NDRs). The vias are based on the wire-widths of the rout-
       ing-rule and are created to meet all the DRC via enclosure  rules  with
       variations  for good pin-access, variations of double-cut vias for good
       double-cut via utilization, and min-area vias required for stacked-vias
       that have no route connected to them to meet the min-area metal rule.

       This command should be used before init_design, in which case the  vias
       will be created during the initial netlist load. If you change the set-
       tings  after  loading  the  design, you will need to use saveDesign/re-
       storeDesign to trigger the auto-generation of vias with  the  new  set-
       tings. If you want to experiment with different settings inside one In-
       novus session, use generateVias instead.

       The  command requires correct DRC rules (e.g. enclosure, spacing, mini-
       mum-cut, min-area rules, etc), and at least one  LEF  VIARULE  GENERATE
       statement  (or  OpenAccess standardViaDef) for every via layer used for
       routing. The cut enclosure values in the VIARULE GENERATE statement are
       not used except for old LEF  technology  files  (LEF  version  5.5  and
       older) that have no enclosure rules (this is not recommended usage, but
       is kept for backward compatability). The VIARULE cut-spacing values are
       ignored-only the DRC cut-spacing values are used.

       No predefined vias are required (e.g LEF VIA DEFAULT, or NONDEFAULTRULE
       USEVIA  is  not necessary, and OpenAccess routing ConstraintGroup (NDR)
       definitions do not require any validVias list).

       If there are predefined vias, the generated vias are  compared  to  the
       predefined  vias and if they are geometrically identical, that specific
       generated via is not kept so no duplicate vias  are  created.  In  that
       case  a combination of pre-defined and auto-generated vias will be used
       by nanoroute.

       The auto-generated vias are created as parameterized vias  rather  than
       fixed  vias (e.g. VIA using VIARULE rather than RECT statements in DEF,
       or an OpenAccess standardVia rather than customVia).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each setGenerateViaMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setGenerateViaMode.

       -reset Resets all or specified options to default value.

              Any  values  that do not already match the default value and are
              reset will be reported.

       -auto {true|false}
              Enables auto via generation when design is loaded. The option is
              of type bool.

              Default: false

       -ndr_only {true|false}
              Generates vias for non default rules only.

              Default:  false

Example
              * setGenerateViaMode -auto true

                Will add auto-generated vias to  any  existing  vias  for  all
                routing rules when the design is loaded.

See also:
              * dumpOutVias to write out the vias

              * generateVias to generate vias in the current Innovus session

              * Design Implementation Flow chapter of Innovus User Guide.

